headline: Why Palantir Stock Is Sinking Today
summary: A report last week from The Times detailed Palantir's close ties to the Trump administration, leading to a surge in its stock price.  CEO Alex Karp refuted one of the report's core assertions, leading to today's decline.  A report last week from The New York Times asserted, among other things, that Palantir, which leverages artificial intelligence (AI) to analyze massive data sets and help clients make better decisions, has gained incredible access to data across the federal government, which could give President Donald Trump "untold surveillance power."
